 The fire in Du Toit s Kloof Pass spread rapidly during the night and fire crews did well to prevent the fire from damaging any property '' said Cape Winelands Incident Commander Heinrich Louw.Aerial support has been activated in the area with four choppers currently water bombing the fire in conjunction with 120 fire men fighting the blaze on the ground. Sixteen fire trucks have also been strategically placed on the ground with three skid units.Three houses were evacuated on Thursday night at about 7pm but residents have since returned to their home.Du Toits Kloof Pass remains closed and motorists will have to make use of Huguenot Tunnel.Firefighting operations are expected continue throughout Friday.